HEADWORD: Clumper
<hw>Clump"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>kl⟦uum⟧mpern</ets> to clod. See <er>Clump</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To form into clumps or masses.</def>
